HEADWORD: bioflavinoid
<hw>bi`o*flav"in*oid</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a vitamin that maintains
the resistance of cell and capillary walls to permeation; -- called also
<altname>vitamin P</altname> and <altname>citrin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

